My take-home message from today's fail was the American spelling of FLIER, which is much more interesting, for me.

@Steve L 

If you do your Ngrams again, with "post a flier", to try to isolate the specific usage for [Handbill], you'll find that that usage has taken off quite dramatically in AmE in the last few decades, but not in BrE. That fits with my own perception, that "flyer" is strongly preferred in this context.
The numbers are small, but they suggest that AmE is currently fairly happy to call a handbill a "flier", whereas BrE wants to stick with "flyer". Or so it seems to me.

